## Model fitting
<div class="black">
```{r, results='asis', echo = F}
### Trial of regression model
# Multiple regression adding on new created predictors 
mod_mar_age2 <- lm(Marriage_age ~ Wealth_index_ + Residence + Women_Educational_level_ 
                   + Husband_Educational_level_ + Age_difference 
                   + Highest_educational_year_difference, data = myanm.df)

summ(mod_mar_age2, confint = TRUE, digit =3) %>%
  tidy() %>%
  mutate(term = c("Intercept", "WI - Poorer","WI - Middle","WI - Richer","WI - Richest",
                  "Rural residency", "Women EL- Secondary","Women EL - Higher",
                  "Husband EL - Secondary","Husband EL - Higher","Age difference", 
                  "Educational year difference"),
         var = c(NA, "Wealth_index_", NA, NA, NA, "Residence", "Women_Educational_level_",
                 NA, "Husband_Educational_level_", NA, "Age_difference",
                 "Highest_educational_year_difference")) %>%
        select(term, estimate, conf.low, conf.high, p.value ) %>%
      kable(digits = 3,
      caption = "Regression model for predicting marriage age of female", 
      booktabs = T) %>%
  kable_styling(position = "center") %>%
   footnote(general = "WI; Wealth index, EL; educational level ")
     
```

# Discussion
## Wealth index
<div class="black">
<div class="red2">**Higher than "middle"** class was associated with **low marriage age** </div>  


- Arranged marriage by parents

- Utilize for Financial security

- Expect betrothal gift money

[@rumble2018empirical] [@kidman2016child]

## Education
<div class="black">
<div class="red2">**Less educated** women and her husbands were likely to **marry earlier**</div>  


- Financial issue for tuition

- Lack of reprocutive health knowledge

- Drop out secondary to early birth 

[@mehra2018effectiveness]

## Gender inequality
<div class="black">
<div class="red2">**Difference in age and education** **reduced** age at marriage of women.</div>  


- Men who have musculine ideologies prefer younger wife

- Male-dominated education 

[@sandoy2016effectiveness][@rumble2018empirical][@kidman2016child]

## Limitation
<div class="black">
- Cross sectional study design

- Missing values

- Potential other confounders

# Conclusion
## Conclusion
<div class="black">
The difference in the highest educational level between women and their husbands were associated to age at first marriage in women in Myanmar in addition to factors of individual educational level, wealth index and age difference between them. 

